headline: TFC Q1 Deep Dive: Expense Discipline Amid Revenue Headwinds and Strategic Growth Investments
summary: Financial services company Truist Financial (NYSE:TFC) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 1.7% year on year to $4.9 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.87 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
